body:
Thank you Jo, your suggestion helped me as well... had same problem when wanting to run tests from Symfony services/controllers.

 here's code in case anyone would be having same issue.

`
        define('PHPUNIT_TESTSUITE', 1); //this line helped me with hiding output using obj_start etc.
        $_SERVER['KERNEL_DIR'] =  dirname(getcwd()) . '/app/'; //this line helped me with  ' You must override the KernelTestCase::createKernel() method.'
        $testsPath = dirname(getcwd()).'/tests/Integration/';

```
    ob_start();
    $phpunit = new \PHPUnit_TextUI_TestRunner;
     $suite = $phpunit->getTest($testsPath, '', 'Test.php');
    $test_results = $phpunit->doRun($suite, ['--debug' ], false);
    $output = ob_get_clean();
```

`

Ok, got it. Then we will need another constant to hook in and disable the default output buffer consumption or another approach it seems.

Maybe something like:

``` php
while (
    !defined('PHPUNIT_TESTSUITE')
    && !defined('PHPUNIT_NO_OP_CONSUMPTION')
    && ob_get_level() > 0
) {
    ob_end_clean();
}
```

Does this patch solve your problem?

```
diff --git a/src/Framework/TestCase.php b/src/Framework/TestCase.php
index af0d1c5..08834ad 100644
--- a/src/Framework/TestCase.php
+++ b/src/Framework/TestCase.php
@@ -2346,10 +2346,6 @@ protected function getMockObjectGenerator()
      */
     private function startOutputBuffering()
     {
-        while (!defined('PHPUNIT_TESTSUITE') && ob_get_level() > 0) {
-            ob_end_clean();
-        }
-
         ob_start();

         $this->outputBufferingActive = true;
@@ -2362,7 +2358,7 @@ private function startOutputBuffering()
     private function stopOutputBuffering()
     {
         if (ob_get_level() != $this->outputBufferingLevel) {
-            while (ob_get_level() > 0) {
+            while (ob_get_level() >= $this->outputBufferingLevel) {
                 ob_end_clean();
             }
```
